{"key":"processedPost-13883519","value":{"id":13883519,"first":13882540,"last":13889477,"when":1296521880,"utime":"02/01/11 02:58 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>skuzzy1232 said:</b><br />just cold shock em to wake em back up. the only risk iv had is sometimes they fruit in the jar which is cool as fuck .in those cases i break the jar pick em and fruit<br /></blockquote><br /><br />This is very bad advice.&nbsp; Unless people say otherwise, they're growing cubes, and cubes don't benefit from a cold shock, nor does any other mushroom which fruits in semi-tropical areas in the summer.&nbsp; In addition, if fruits form in the grain jars, they can be spawned right to bulk with the rest of the grains.&nbsp; There is no need or reason to break the jars.<br /><br />To the OP, yes casing is required if you're wanting to use grains as your substrate.&nbsp; Here's a <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Casing-Layer-Preparation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">mushroom casing video clip</a> to walk you through the casing prep.&nbsp; It's only a sample clip, but should give you the idea.&nbsp; The full tek is on the DVD.<br />RR","title":"Re: Casing necessary?"}}